  * Fission power production given a nice boost (all input types). Power output values now range between 9 to 70 per unit of fuel, depending on the type of fuel used)

  -- Quests --
  * Vina's House now has a teleporter, allowing easier access for he and Welchie's quests as well as Science Outpost access
  * Vina now gives you access to the Science Outpost immediately after you create your Machining Table

  -- Biomes --
  * unknown worlds now have biome hazards randomly generated on first arrival by a player, allowing for worlds to have 2 to 5 additional hazards

  -- Misc --
  * Matmod placer has been improved in feel and appearance
  * Miniknog and Cultist NPCs now have standardized loadouts, based on tier, rather than RNG weapons
  * Defense Turret damages increased for all types other than Gauss
  * Renamed seeds that are called the same as produce to avoid confusion
  * Completing the Dark Cavern and Ship Repair quests should now unlock terramart/enhanced storage, etc, rather than leaving it till after Erchius Mine. Revisiting the outpost will reveal them as open.
  * tricorder now has more detailed display for when FR is 'off'
  * Mech Fuel Consumption rates have been reduced by 40%
  * Ores no longer extract for research
  * Water Tower works a bit faster than the farmwell.
  * More outputs added to Rock Crusher
  * Garden Worlds now spawn 4/4 bee types, rather than 3/4
  * corrected various typos
  * Glow Glass is made in batches of 10 rather than 1, for the same cost
  * Removed both subs from the Vehicle shop to encourage building them
  * cheapened vehicle controller units to avoid research cheesing
  * Liquid Condenser swapped to use a json object file for recipes rather than lua
  * Rock Breaker now appears in the Lab directory
  * Rail Crafting table is properly craftable again
  * adjusted Hydrolium recipe to be less taxing
  * revised meleecombo.lua: now uses a caching system to store tag data, marginal ease of use and performance improvement.
  * Lasombrium Node now tells where to make the Lasombrium
  * Lasombrium recipe simplified. Second recipe removed to avoid confusion

